The @MyTaliaJewelry pop-up store in NYC offers perfect necklaces and earrings that will elevate any outfit!

@EdenYoungstein visited the pop-up store and met the founder and creative director @Tal_Man_1.

Continue reading for @EdenYoungstein’s experience: 

“I recently visited the @MyTaliaJewelry pop-up store at @FlyingSoloNYC, located in Soho, NY and met up with my longtime favorite jewelry designer, @Tal_Man_1! It was so fun checking out her new charms and together we picked out the perfect ones I needed to add to my growing collection! I absolutely love her charms because I can customize and layer them on both my necklaces and earrings!”

Visit the @MyTaliaJewelry pop-up store in @FlyingSoloNYC located at 📍420 West Broadway, Manhattan.

If you can’t make it to the pop-up, visit the @MyTaliaJewelry website via the link in their bio to shop pre-set necklaces and earrings or to create your own in their virtual atelier.

🌾My Creation VS My Inspiration ✨ (—>swipe)
_________________________________
Swipe to see my main inspiration! What do you think of my twist on the idea? I cannot believe that it’s been almost a year since I made this Bohemian Garden Tea Party for Gracie and Matt; who happen to share the same birthday. I decided to do this fun, whimsical and elegant summer theme in celebration of Gracie’s First Birthday 🥳 Matt didn’t mind as long as he got his BBQ. I created reels last year about how I made the floral chandeliers as well as the party itself, but now I wanted to share my inspiration to show you how easy it can be to DIY sometimes 💪🏼 what do you think of the outcome? 
_________________________________
I got my inspiration off of Google, so O don’t know who to credit. If you do, tag them and I’ll update my post!

Trying not to blink. 💐 
_________________________________
Spent yesterday in a magical state being present, taking in every moment and being grateful for what I truly have in this world - these chickens 🐣 Unconditional love is so priceless. 
We took the first half of the day and visited family before heading out to Dumbo where we took these pictures. Then I put my phone away for the day. We spent time walking around, going to the park, playing games, enjoying each other’s company and eating ice cream and pizza that was just out of this world! ✨

Casual Everyday Outfit Inspired by Colorful Art.
_____________________________________________

*I don’t think I’ll ever get used to the camera. 

We FINALLY put up this beautiful artwork by Romero Britto — my current favorite. It brings so much color and life into the room, don’t you think? Here’s a casual outfit inspired by it. It’s both basic and extra - the fine line I strive to linger on every day. 
_____________________________________________
I’ve recently talked about the importance of good quality basic clothing on my broadcast channel. It’s so important for us to have durable clothing in our wardrobe, but it’s also important for the Earth. If you’re going to buy something new to wear, remind yourself that you’re buying to keep and if it’s not love at first sight, it’s probably not worth it.

🌿 Can anyone guess what type of plant I’m holding? 
________________________________
I loveeee my new plant @tal_gerber_style thank you 😘 
________________________________
A solid colored short suit is one of my go-to basics. Why? I can wear any top and type of belt and it will still look and make me feel great 🤩 💯 
Part of me REALLY wants to add a vest - but it might just be too hot … maybe I’ll revisit that idea in the fall 🤔 
_________________________________
My way of being sustainable in fashion: It’s creating new looks using what I already have. There is absolutely no reason we need to keep filling landfills with low quality clothing. If I buy something new, I’m going to buy what I know is quality enough to last me and what I know I will wear, re-use and keep. If your taste in clothing is like mine, add color to your basics to make them more fun! 🤩 
_________________________________
Btw, has anyone started planting in their gardens yet? What did you plant?

Their birth months are consecutively 4 months apart from each other and this necklace is a physical portrayal of my never ending love for them; every quarter, year round, forever.
